    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Mouth-blown bagpipes of Scotland, having a sheepskin bag, conical double-reed chanter, three drone pipes, and a blowpipe.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000026541/Marcuse, Musical Instruments Dictionary (1975)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Gaitas escocesas de boca que tienen un depósito de piel de oveja, un tubo melódico cónico con lengüeta doble, tres roncones y un tubo para soplar el aire.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
